input.prompt:
You are configuring nginx to serve CortexBuild Ultimate on port 80.

## Context
- React frontend built to /var/www/cortexbuild-ultimate/dist/
- Express API running on localhost:3001 via PM2
- The vite.config.ts may have a base path configured — check it
- This is a Ubuntu/Debian server

## Your Task

### Step 1: Check if nginx is installed
  nginx -v 2>&1
If not installed: apt-get install -y nginx

### Step 2: Build the frontend
  cd /var/www/cortexbuild-ultimate && npm run build
Check if dist/ exists and has index.html after build.

### Step 3: Check vite.config.ts
Read /var/www/cortexbuild-ultimate/vite.config.ts to understand the base path and any proxy settings.

### Step 4: Write nginx config
Create /etc/nginx/sites-available/cortexbuild with:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;

    root /var/www/cortexbuild-ultimate/dist;
    index index.html;

    # API proxy — forward /api/* to Express backend
    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
        client_max_body_size 50M;
    }

    # Static file uploads
    location /uploads/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
    }

    # SPA fallback — all other routes serve index.html
    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }

    # Cache static assets
    location ~* \.(js|css|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|svg|woff|woff2|ttf|eot)$ {
        expires 1y;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }
}

### Step 5: Enable the site
  ln -sf /etc/nginx/sites-available/cortexbuild /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/cortexbuild
  rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
  nginx -t
  systemctl enable nginx
  systemctl restart nginx

### Step 6: Verify
  curl -s http://localhost/api/health
  curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost/

If the health check returns {"status":"ok","version":"1.0.0"} and the frontend returns 200, it's working.

### Step 7: Fix any issues
Common issues:
- If nginx -t fails, check the config syntax carefully
- If API returns 502, check PM2: pm2 list, pm2 restart cortexbuild-api
- If frontend returns 404, check the dist/ path exists

Return a summary of what was configured and the final verification results (both curl outputs).

